{"section": "3.13.1: Using the well-ordering principle.", "qid": 0, "instructions": "<div class=\"activity-instructions\">\n <p>\n  The well-ordering principle can be used to prove any fact which can be proven by standard or strong induction.\n </p>\n <p>\n  Consider again the problem of purchasing cans of juice. Suppose that juice is sold in 2-packs or 5-packs. Let Q(n) be the statement that it is possible to buy n cans of juice by combining 2-packs and 5-packs. We can use the principle of well-ordering to show that for\n  <span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n   n \u2265 4,\n  </span>\n  Q(n) is true.\n </p>\n</div>\n", "question": "<div class=\"question\">\n <div class=\"setup flex-row\">\n  <div class=\"label\">\n   1)\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"text\">\n   To which set should the well-ordering principle be applied?\n  </div>\n </div>\n <fieldset>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember98\" style=\"\">\n   <input aria-label=\"The set of all n \u2265 1 such that Q(n) is false.\" name=\"11\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember97&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"\">\n    The set of all n \u2265 1 such that Q(n) is false.\n   </label>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember100\" style=\"\">\n   <input aria-label=\"The set of all n \u2265 4 such that Q(n) is true.\" name=\"11\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember99&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"\">\n    The set of all n \u2265 4 such that Q(n) is true.\n   </label>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember102\" style=\"\">\n   <input aria-label=\"The set of all n \u2265 4 such that Q(n) is false.\" name=\"11\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember101&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"\">\n    The set of all n \u2265 4 such that Q(n) is false.\n   </label>\n  </div>\n </fieldset>\n</div>\n", "choices": ["<div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember98\">\n <input aria-label=\"The set of all n \u2265 1 such that Q(n) is false.\" name=\"11\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember97&gt;\"/>\n <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  The set of all n \u2265 1 such that Q(n) is false.\n </label>\n</div>\n", "<div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember100\">\n <input aria-label=\"The set of all n \u2265 4 such that Q(n) is true.\" name=\"11\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember99&gt;\"/>\n <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  The set of all n \u2265 4 such that Q(n) is true.\n </label>\n</div>\n", "<div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember102\">\n <input aria-label=\"The set of all n \u2265 4 such that Q(n) is false.\" name=\"11\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember101&gt;\"/>\n <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  The set of all n \u2265 4 such that Q(n) is false.\n </label>\n</div>\n"], "answer": "The set of all n \u2265 4 such that Q(n) is false.", "explanation": "<div aria-atomic=\"true\" class=\"explanation has-explanation correct\" role=\"alert\">\n <p class=\"message\">\n  Correct\n </p>\n The set should include all integers n that violate that fact to be proven. An integer n violates the fact to be proven if n \u2265 4 and Q(n) is false.\n</div>\n"}